parameters:
Clea: Relm taught us the courage to never give up and the
courage to keep pushing forward, supporting our new dreams.

Mage Relm: I'll teach you many times! Oh, how about we meet
on your birthday! It would be nice to celebrate the day we
first met too, and have a housewarming party again...

Clea: If you want to meet, let's meet. We are friends, so we
don't need a special reason.

Mage Relm: Sigh, yes, let's play again... Thank you for
becoming my first friend...

Thief Nora: It feels like a lie to say goodbye. Since we've
been together for so long, I thought we would continue to be
together from now on.

Mage Relm: It's tough to say goodbye since we both have
dreams to fulfill... but we are friends!

Mage Relm: Even if we're apart, our hearts are connected.
Whenever you need the talent of a genius, please rely on me!

Thief Nora: I'll rely on you even when I need a friend!
Let's eat together, talk, and eat again!

Mage Relm: This great genius has returned to the Magic
Academy!

Mage Relm: Please prepare to give up that seat. I will
definitely fulfill my new dream that I have grasped with my
friends!

\CL 【After Mage Relm】Relm, the mage, diligently conducted
research at the Magic Academy and was promoted to a senior
sorcerer. Unlike in the past, she now focuses on fieldwork
for her magical studies.

\CL From her travel experiences, Relm, the mage, conducted
research and development not only on unconventional magic
circles but also collaborated with other mages and
occasionally even with priests.

\CL Research was always conducted with the policy of for
someone's sake.

\CL She became an Archmage at a young age and built a grand
library. As a result, after her death, she was revered as
the Archmage of Love for Books and respected.

\CL She married a younger researcher and gave birth to a
talented girl.

\CL 【After Archmage】Devoting her entire life to not
provoking the hero and maintaining the neutrality of the
Magic Academy, she passed away seven years after reclaiming
the throne.

\CL His ideals were passed down to the future Magic Academy,
and there was never a crisis like the disappearance of the
old Magic Academy.

\CL As expected, after his death, he was called the Archmage
of Summoning.

Researcher Dokusa: The world may be facing a crisis! Relm-
kun, I need your cooperation again!

\CL 【After Researcher Dokusa】Due to his caring nature, he
was appointed as a lecturer at the Magic Academy. Despite
being eccentric, he was a delightful and kind instructor who
was very popular.

\CL She opened the doors of the once exclusive Magic Academy
by facilitating research positions for those without magical
talent.

\CL It was a life of constantly running for the sake of the
students until she fell ill.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

You won't be able to come back, but are you really leaving
the room?
Clea (We haven't talked yet, have we?)

Mage Relm: Huff, huff, thank you for stopping me back then!
I will definitely become an Arcmage that everyone can be
proud of!

Mage Relm: Let's meet again, let's meet many times...
Because everyone is a truly important friend that I made for
the first time!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea: Thank you very much for your cooperation, even though
you were supposed to be neutral.

Archmage: Well, what is this about... The Magic Academy is
neutral, no matter what happens.

Archmage: I'm truly grateful to you for stopping Relm-kun,
who has been a great help to all of you.

Thief Nora: He may have been a perverted person, but thank
you very much for helping us so much!

Archmage: I won't deny it... but today, I intend to be
serious.

Thief Nora: So, it turns out you were just pretending to be
senile after all! Just as Sophia-san and Relm-san said!

Researcher Dokusa: Parting may be painful, but don't worry.
Your bond is not weak enough to be severed by distance
alone.
